        "title": "Static method call from JUnit test without specifying class",
        "body": "<p>Is it possible to call a static method from a junit test without specifying it's class?<\/p>\n\n<p>The following code works:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>package lightsOut;\n\nimport static org.junit.Assert.*;\nimport org.junit.Test;\nimport lightsOut.LightsOutModel;\n\npublic class LightsOutModelTest {\n\n    @Test\n    public void testLightsOutModel1(){\n        assertTrue(LightsOutModel.checkWin()); // Note here\n    }\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>But when I remove the class from the following line it shows an error.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>        assertTrue(checkWin()); // Note here\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The error is: <br><i>The method checkWin() is undefined for the type LightsOutModelTest<\/i><\/p>\n\n<p>Do I always have to specify the class on the static method call? Isn't there a way to import all the methods from the class because the way I tried to do it doesn't seem to work?<\/p>\n",
